	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice post Saddil. One thing I want to add that is very important: choose targets that are "social". That means that they will not run away if they get low health -- they will stick together and not desert eachother. A good example of social creatures are Kobolds in Stonebrunt or Ulthorks/walruses in Eastern Wastes. <br><br>The worst thing is AE nuking 3 or 4 mobs, then one starts to wander off while you are still kiting the others becuase they were partial resists or had more HPs. Then you have to try to stay close so you dont loose track of the wanderer, AE nuke the others down, and hope you have mana for individually finishing these off. By the time you hunt down the wanderers you have lost much of your time/mana efficiency.<br><br>One tip for if BoF is resisted. Cast Tishans Clash on the one that resisted. This stun is just about long enough for you to recast BoF and for the others to catch up to it, so you only have to run around the critters 2 times or so to regroup. Then AE nuke and re-BoF just so they all have the same snare time left.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
