	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 4th 8:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Basic skills I do for any class:<br>Baking:&nbsp;&nbsp;Not a big money-maker, but since they added stats to food I've gotten all of my chars over 50.  The dex/agi from something as simple as rat kabobs is a nice bonus (26 triv, buy the rat meat from Ping in WFP or make some newbies kick themselves by offering 2pp/stack, the skewers are usually available on any of the merchants near the forge in EFP)  And the +2str on beer braised bear or gator will usually get a couple plat from the tank-types.  <br>Smithing:  My main is a master smith, my alts usually develop a little skill sharpening rusties, but that's about it.  (Banded and forged bastard swords/2handers can be a good money maker on a newer server or you can bind in Everfrost and gate to WC/NRo - not too many people selling large banded to the big uglies)<br>Tailoring:  I get to at least 40 making silk threads/patchwork/tailored large bags for sale or personal use.  Once I get tailoring to the high 30s, any LQ/MQ pelts get turned into leather padding because - Making studded stinks!  Although the bearskin potion bags are tough if you skip studded and they are handy for storing research components.  If you do struggle through studded there's some money to be made on cured silk, backpacks and Wu's.<br>Brewing/Pottery:  If you're going to really get into tailoring you'll probably want to get these up as well for Heady Kiolas (cured silks/Wu's) and the vials needed for Viscous mana (Wu's)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
