	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey, I don't even play a wizard (had a lvl 3 for a while, but deleted him) but I'm bored as H311&nbsp;&nbsp;here at work so thought i'd post.<br><br>In the past i've been an Erudite junky.  Of course they have the highest base INT which always ended up winning me over.  The vision sucks, though, and i really had no idea how big of a difference it was til i started my first inkie.  the difference is HUGE, but IMO is still a matter of convenience.  most classes eventually get spells that give you at least infravision (seeing like a gnome or HE) plus there are items that can help out (stein of moggok comes to mind).  but, if you'd just rather not deal with it, go with the DE.<br><br>personally, i despise high elves.  not sure why, i just can't stand the way they look.  well the HE girls aren't bad, but i don't like playing girl chars much.<br><br>i wouldn't mind being a gnome, i'm secure enough with myself to be 'crotch high' while i'm playing.  i've never played one but i think my next caster will be one.<br><br>and, like i said, i love the ultravision on my DE, and the stats are still very nice.  obviously the drawback here is the faction.  so, in conclusion ... these are my 3 caster races:<br><br>Erudite - still my fav for the great INT, plus they seem a bit rarer, which i like also.<br><br>Dark Elves - a close second right now.  good starting location, close to EC (center of Norrath), still great INT, and of course, ultravision.<br><br>Gnomes - never played one, but i'm getting curiouser and curiouser.  they seem fun and so close to the ground it feels like you always have SoW. =P  <br><br>Anyhow, i've rambled enough.  so much personal opinion it really just boils down to that.  guess i'll head back to work now.  have fun!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
